ext":"0"},"duration":199,"url":"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta/One+More+Love/One+Love","name":"One Love","@attr":{"rank":10},"artist":{"url":"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta","name":"David Guetta","mbid":"302bd7b9-d012-4360-897a-93b00c855680"}},{"streamable":{"fulltrack":"0","#text":"0"},"duration":204,"url":"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta/One+More+Love/I+Wanna+Go+Crazy","name":"I Wanna Go Crazy","@attr":{"rank":11},"artist":{"url":"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta","name":"David Guetta","mbid":"302bd7b9-d012-4360-897a-93b00c855680"}},{"streamable":{"fulltrack":"0","#text":"0"},"duration":225,"url":"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta+&+Tocadisco+feat.+Chris+Willis/One+More+Love/Sound+Of+Letting+Go","name":"Sound Of Letting Go","@attr":{"rank":12},"artist":{"url":"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta+&+Tocadisco+feat.+Chris+Willis","name":"David Guetta & Tocadisco feat. Chris Willis","mbid":""}},{"streamable":{"fulltrack":"0","#text":"0"},"duration":196,"url":"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta+&+Afrojack+Feat.+Wynter+Gordon/One+More+Love/Toyfriend","name":"Toyfriend","@attr":{"rank":13},"artist":{"url":"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta+&+Afrojack+Feat.+Wynter+Gordon","name":"David Guetta & Afrojack Feat. Wynter Gordon","mbid":""}},{"streamable":{"fulltrack":"0","#text":"0"},"duration":280,"url":"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta+feat.+Makeba/One+More+Love/If+We+Ever","name":"If We Ever","@attr":{"rank":14},"artist":{"url":"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta+feat.+Makeba","name":"David Guetta feat. Makeba","mbid":""}}]},"url":"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta/One+More+Love","name":"One More Love","listeners":"1685342","wiki":{"published":"07 Jul 2024, 08:26","summary":"One More Love is the reissue of the fourth studio album by French DJ David Guetta, released in 26 November 2010 through Virgin Records and EMI France. Guetta's first major international release, the original album received generally favourable reviews from music critics, and was a commercial success, selling over 3 million copies globally. It spawned a total of six worldwide hit singles throughout 2009 and 2010, most notably \"When Love Takes Over\", featuring American recording artist Kelly Rowland, \"Sexy Bitch\", featuring Senegalese-American R&B singer Akon, and \"One Love\", featuring British recording artist Estelle; the reissue also given \"Who's That Chick?\", <a href=\"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta/One+More+Love\">Read more on Last.fm</a>.","content":"One More Love is the reissue of the fourth studio album by French DJ David Guetta, released in 26 November 2010 through Virgin Records and EMI France. Guetta's first major international release, the original album received generally favourable reviews from music critics, and was a commercial success, selling over 3 million copies globally. It spawned a total of six worldwide hit singles throughout 2009 and 2010, most notably \"When Love Takes Over\", featuring American recording artist Kelly Rowland, \"Sexy Bitch\", featuring Senegalese-American R&B singer Akon, and \"One Love\", featuring British recording artist Estelle; the reissue also given \"Who's That Chick?\", featuring Barbadian recording artist Rihanna, as a hit single. One Love is also Guetta's last studio album to feature his long-time collaborator, Chris Willis, on vocals. Since the album's initial release, in addition to the new deluxe edition in November 2010, it has since been reissued several times to include previously unreleased tracks and other bonus material. The album received a nomination for the 52nd Grammy Awards in the category Best Electronic/Dance Album. The original album's lead single, \"When Love Takes Over\" was nominated in the categories Best Dance Recording and Best Remixed Recording, Non-Classical, and won the latter. <a href=\"https://www.last.fm/music/David+Guetta/One+More+Love\">Read more on Last.fm</a>. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply."}}}